39424193.review:
This is a good brazilian indie game, but I can only recommend for people who likes tactical turn-based RPG and Sentai stuff (For example Power Rangers).
It's very pleasant to play, specially if you like lighthearted games with puns, with okay pixelated graphics;
Gameplay wise, I'm very satisfated to play a game which I can customize my squad choosing them from a list at the start of the game, and every tiny bity like squad name, transformation name etc; 
It's very easy to pick and does well to be unique in the strategical aspect.
It has a system that you gain money and resources based on your performance after each battle if you follow the "script", which I don't like much in harder difficulties of the game (in easier ones it's pretty fine), because it becomes snowbally and you can't handle at certain point if you didn't min/max;
In a personal note, I think they could let go the references of their "friends" and put better ones (like a sword from someone called João is awkward compared to a sword from some nice reference for International audience).

